<TITLE> DU's Zia Hall provost quits over clashes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 9 (bdnews24.com)  The provost of President Ziaur Rahman Hall of Dhaka University, Prof Borhan Uddin Khan, has resigned his position taking responsibility for the clashes at the hall, the vice-chancellor said on Friday. "The law faculty dean Prof Borhan has resigned from his position of provost of Ziaur Rahman Hall," Prof SMA Faiz told bdnews24.com. In his resignation letter, Prof Borhan, the pro-BNP teacher, said, "I along with house tutors of the hall tried in vain to control the hall situation. So I'm resigning." The university's provost committee has appointed Prof Mahfuzul Haq of accounting, a house tutor of the hall, acting provost, the VC said. The hall has seen sporadic clashes between two rival factions of Awami League-backed student body Bangladesh Chhatra League since the AL has won in the ninth general election on Dec. 29. On Thursday the two factions were involved in overnight clashes at the hall that left four injured while police made seven arrests from the spot. bd
